<h2>Focus Trap Adapter</h2>
<p>
    The Focus Trap Adapter bridges the <a href="https://github.com/focus-trap/focus-trap">focus-trap</a>
    library to Web Everything's <a href="/intents/focus-containment/">Focus Containment Intent</a>, so a
    consumer already on <code>focus-trap</code> can drive it through the intent's declarative vocabulary
    (<code>trap</code> / <code>background</code> / <code>initialFocus</code> / <code>restore</code>) instead
    of hand-writing options.
</p>

<section class="section-card fui-card">
    <h3 id="status">Status</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
        <strong>Proof of Concept:</strong> a dependency-free bridge exists in Frontier UI
        (<code>adapters/focus-trap/focusTrapAdapter.ts</code>) with a full unit suite. The library is
        <em>injected</em>, not depended on — native <code>&lt;dialog&gt;.showModal()</code> +
        <code>inert</code> remain the recommended default; this adapter is the opt-in path for consumers who
        have already chosen <code>focus-trap</code>.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="section-card fui-card">
    <h3 id="concept">Concept</h3>
    <p>
        The adapter is a pure data transform in both directions plus a small runtime seam. The four intent
        dimensions project onto <code>focus-trap</code>'s options, and a trap instance is adapted to the
        intent's <code>contain</code> / <code>release</code> event contract:
    </p>

    {% highlight "typescript" %}
import { createFocusTrap } from 'focus-trap';
import { createContainment } from '@web-adapters/focus-trap';

// The library is injected — the adapter never imports focus-trap itself.
const containment = createContainment(createFocusTrap, '#dialog', {
    trap: 'trap',            // confine focus to the surface
    background: 'inert',     // seal off the rest of the page
    initialFocus: 'first-tabbable',
    restore: 'restore',      // return focus to the trigger on close
});

containment.contain();  // → focus-trap activate()
containment.release();  // → focus-trap deactivate()
    {% endhighlight %}

    <p>
        <code>toFocusTrapOptions(intent)</code> is the deterministic downward projection;
        <code>fromFocusTrapOptions(options)</code> is the inverse (recovering the intent from an existing
        trap config, preserving any unmapped option as residual). Consumers never bind to focus-trap's
        option names — swapping to the native <code>&lt;dialog&gt;</code> baseline is an intent-level change,
        not a rewrite.
    </p>
</section>

